      "all_verified": true,
      "proof_text": "ALGEBRAIC PROOF OF QUASI-LINEARITY\n==================================================\n\nTheorem: W(S) = h_i(S, q_{-i}) + \u03bb\u00b7q_i\u00b7\ud835\udfd9[i\u2208S]\n\nStep 1: Sinkhorn divergence independence from q_i\n  div(S) = -S_\u03b5(\u03bc_S, \u03bd) depends only on embeddings {x_i}.\n  The Sinkhorn algorithm solves:\n    u \u2190 a / (K\u00b7v),  v \u2190 b / (K^T\u00b7u)\n  where K = exp(-C/\u03b5), C_ij = \u2016x_i - x_j\u2016\u00b2.\n  None of these depend on reported qualities {q_i}.\n  VERIFIED: max |div(perturbed) - div(base)| = 0.00e+00\n  Status: PASS \u2713\n\nStep 2: Dual potential independence from q_i\n  (f, g) solve the dual OT program over (\u03bc_S, \u03bd).\n  Since \u03bc_S = (1/|S|)\u00b7\u03a3_{i\u2208S} \u03b4_{x_i}, the potentials\n  depend only on {x_i} and \u03bd, not on {q_i}.\n  VERIFIED: max |potential change| = 0.00e+00\n  Status: PASS \u2713\n\nStep 3: Exact quasi-linear decomposition\n  W(S) = (1-\u03bb)\u00b7div(S) + \u03bb\u00b7\u03a3_{j\u2208S} q_j\n       = [(1-\u03bb)\u00b7div(S) + \u03bb\u00b7\u03a3_{j\u2260i} q_j] + \u03bb\u00b7q_i\u00b7\ud835\udfd9[i\u2208S]\n       = h_i(S, q_{-i}) + \u03bb\u00b7q_i\u00b7\ud835\udfd9[i\u2208S]\n  This is exact since div(S) has zero dependence on q_i.\n  VERIFIED: max |W_actual - W_predicted| = 1.87e-16\n  Status: PASS \u2713\n\nConclusion: The quasi-linearity identity is an EXACT algebraic\nproperty, not an approximation. The < 1e-8 error in numerical\nverification is due to floating-point arithmetic (IEEE 754),\nnot mathematical imprecision."
    },
